Chilean Stocks: Colbun, Corpbanca, Copec, Empresas La Polar

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-05-04T19:43:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-04/chilean-stocks-colbun-empresas-copec-and-empresas-la-polar.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 3:12 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index fell 1.1 percent to 4,758.66.  Colbun SA (COLBUN)   rose 0.3 percent to 142 pesos.
 Chile ’s third-largest power producer climbed for a second day
after Banco Santander SA increased its recommendation to “buy”
from “hold.”  Corpbanca (CORPBANC)   retreated 1.9 percent to 7.2 pesos,
the steepest loss in a month. Chile’s sixth-largest lender was
reiterated at ”underperform” at Banco Santander SA.  Empresas Copec SA (COPEC)  , Chile’s largest pulp exporter
and the company with the largest weighting on the IPSA index,
fell 1.3 percent to 8,778.8 pesos. Latin American asset prices
are showing early signs of forming bubbles, Miguel Savastano,
deputy director for the Western Hemisphere at the  International
Monetary Fund , said today in Santiago.  Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)   rose 0.8 percent to
2,654.6, its eighth day of gains and longest winning streak in
more than three years. The quality of the Chilean department
store chain’s consumer loans portfolio is improving, and the
company is betting strongly on  Colombia  for its retail
expansion, Chairman Pablo Alcalde said at a conference
yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
